 collated his ideas and symbols of ancient wisdom into the sometimes complex, always rewarding pattern of essays. The Door in the Sky is a collection of the author's writings on myth drawn from his Metaphysics and Traditional Art and Symbolism, both originally published in Bollingen Series. These essays were written while Coomaraswamy was curator in the department of Asiatic Art of the Boston Museum of Fine Arts, where he built the first large collection of Indian art in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aSymbolism in art. 7aART / Asian / General.2bisacsh  aAgni.  aAgnihotra.  aAhir Budhnya.  aBai Ulgan.  aBhadra.  aBrahma(n).  aChavannes, E.  aChrist.  aDante.  aGrail.  aHermes Trismegistus.  aMarsyas.  aNumenius.  aPlato.  aPythagoras.  aQuintilian.  abeatitude.  abreath.  acannibalism.  acomprehensor.  adespiration.  aecstasy.  aeternity.  aevil.  aexemplarism.  afolklore.  agnosis.  agovernment.  aheart.  ahero.  aiconography.  aimagination.  aimmortality.  aindustrialism.  aintellect.  ajudgment of art.  aknowledge.  aliberation.  alotus.  ametaphysics.  amodernism.  anativity.  aoriginality.  aornament.  aparticipation.  apoetry.  aprinciple.  aroof-plate.  asalvation.  ascripture.  aĀditya.1 aCoomaraswamy, Rama P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoomaraswamy, Rama P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691219332zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691219332423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691219